]]''\n|[[Iris Murdoch]]\n|1954\n|-\n|''[[Under the Volcano]]''\n|[[Malcolm Lowry]]\n|1947\n|-\n|''[[Watchmen]]''\n|[[Alan Moore]] and [[Dave Gibbons]]\n|1986\n|-\n|''[[White Noise (novel)|White Noise]]''\n|[[Don DeLillo]]\n|1985\n|-\n|''[[White Teeth]]''\n|[[Zadie Smith]]\n|2000\n|-\n|''[[Wide Sargasso Sea]]''\n|[[Jean Rhys]]\n|1966\n|}\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Le Monde's 100 Books of the Century|''Le Monde'''s 100 Books of the Century]]\n*[[Time's All-Time 100 Movies]]\n\n==External links==\n* [http://entertainment.time.com/2005/10/16/all-time-100-novels/slide/times-list-of-the-100-best-novels/#times-list-of-the-100-best-novels List Description] at Time.com\n* [http://entertainment.time.com/2005/10/16/all-time-100-novels/slide/all/ Full List] at Time.com \n* [http://www.time.com/time/specials/packages/completelist/0,29569,1883296,00.html List description] of the 10 best Graphic Novels at Time.com\n\n{{Books}}\n[[Category:Time (magazine) 100 Lists]]\n[[Category:Lists of novels]]\n[[Category:Top book lists]]\n", "text_old": "{{primary|date=February 2018}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:''Time'''s List of the 100 Best Novels}}\n'''''Time''<nowiki>'</nowiki>s List of the 100 Best Novels''' is an unranked list of the 100 best [[novel]]s published in the English language between 1923 and 2010. The list was compiled by ''[[Time (magazine)|Time Magazine]]'' critics [[Lev Grossman]] and [[Richard Lacayo]].<ref name=\"Time\">{{cite web |url=http://entertainment.time.com/2005/10/16/all-time-100-novels/slide/times-list-of-the-100-best-novels/#all |title=Time's List of the 100 Best Novels (1923\u20132005) |last=Kelly |first=James |author2=Lev Grossman |author3=Richard Lacayo |date=October 16, 2005 |work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]}}</ref> \n\nThe list includes only novels published between 1923 (when ''Time'' was first published) and 2010 (when the list was compiled). As a result, some notable 20th-century novels such as ''[[Ulysses (novel)|Ulysses]]'' by [[James Joyce]] \u2014 published in 1922 \u2014 were ineligible for inclusion.<ref name=\"Time\"/><ref>Richard Lacayo, [http://entertainment.time.com/2005/10/16/all-time-100-novels/ \"How We Picked the List\"], ''Time'', January 6, 2010.</ref>\n\nA list of the ten best [[graphic novels]] of the period was subsequently published as a supplement to the list.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://entertainment.time.com/2009/03/06/top-10-graphic-novels/slide/all/ |title=Top 10 Graphic Novels |last=Grossman |first=Lev |date=October 16, 2005 |work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]}}</ref> ''[[Watchmen]]'' (1986) by [[Alan Moore]] and [[Dave Gibbons]] appears on both the 100 Best Novels and 10 Best Graphic Novels lists, giving the combined lists a total of 109 entries.\n\n== List ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+\n!Title\n!Author\n!Year\n|-\n|''[[The Adventures of Augie March]]''\n|[[Saul Bellow]]\n|1953\n|-\n|''[[All the King\u2019s Men]]''\n|[[Robert Penn Warren]]\n|1946\n|-\n|''[[American Pastoral]]''\n|[[Philip Roth]]\n|1997\n|-\n|''[[An American Tragedy]]''\n|[[Theodore Dreiser]]\n|1925\n|-\n|''[[Animal Farm]]''\n|[[George Orwell]]\n|1946\n|-\n|''[[Appointment in Samarra]]''\n|[[John O'Hara]]\n|1934\n|-\n|''[[Are You There God? It's Me, Margaret.]]''\n|[[Judy Blume]]\n|1970\n|-\n|''[[The Assistant (novel)|The Assistant]]''\n|[[Bernard Malamud]]\n|1957\n|-\n|''[[At Swim-Two-Birds]]''\n|[[Flann O'Brien]]\n|1938\n|-\n|''[[Atonement (novel)|Atonement]]''\n|[[Ian McEwan]]\n|2002\n|-\n|''[[Beloved (novel)|Beloved]]''\n|[[Toni Morrison]]\n|1987\n|-\n|''[[The Berlin Stories]]''\n|[[Christopher Isherwood]]\n|1946\n|-\n|''[[The Big Sleep]]''\n|[[Raymond Chandler]]\n|1939\n|-\n|''[[The Blind Assassin]]''\n|[[Margaret Atwood]]\n|2000\n|-\n|''[[Blood Meridian]]''\n|[[Cormac McCarthy]]\n|1986\n|-\n|''[[Brideshead Revisited]]''\n|[[Evelyn Waugh]]\n|1946\n|-\n|''[[The Bridge of San Luis Rey]]''\n|[[Thornton Wilder]]\n|1927\n|-\n|''[[Call It Sleep]]''\n|[[Henry Roth]]\n|1935\n|-\n|''[[Catch-22]]''\n|[[Joseph Heller]]\n|1961\n|-\n|''[[The Catcher in the Rye]]''\n|[[J. D. Salinger|J.D. Salinger]]\n|1951\n|-\n|''[[A Clockwork Orange (novel)|A Clockwork Orange]]''\n|[[Anthony Burgess]]\n|1963\n|-\n|''[[The Confessions of Nat Turner]]''\n|[[William Styron]]\n|1967\n|-\n|''[[The Corrections]]''\n|[[Jonathan Franzen]]\n|2001\n|-\n|''[[The Crying of Lot 49]]''\n|[[Thomas Pynchon]]\n|1966\n|-\n|''[[A Dance to the Music of Time]]''\n|[[Anthony Powell]]\n|1951\n|-\n|''[[The Day of the Locust]]''\n|[[Nathanael West]]\n|1939\n|-\n|''[[Death Comes for the Archbishop]]''\n|[[Willa Cather]]\n|1927\n|-\n|''[[A Death in the Family]]''\n|[[James Agee]]\n|1958\n|-\n|''[[The Death of the Heart]]''\n|[[Elizabeth Bowen]]\n|1958\n|-\n|''[[Deliverance_(novel)|Deliverance]]''\n|[[James Dickey]]\n|1970\n|-\n|''[[Dog Soldiers (novel)|Dog Soldiers]]''\n|[[Robert Stone (novelist)|Robert Stone]]\n|1974\n|-\n|''[[Falconer (novel)|Falconer]]''\n|[[John Cheever]]\n|1977\n|-\n|''[[The French Lieutenant's Woman]]''\n|[[John Fowles]]\n|1969\n|-\n|''[[The Golden Notebook]]''\n|[[Doris Lessing]]\n|1962\n|-\n|''[[Go Tell It on the Mountain (novel)|Go Tell It on the Mountain]]''\n|[[James Baldwin]]\n|1953\n|-\n|''[[Gone with the Wind (novel)|Gone with the Wind]]''\n|[[Margaret Mitchell]]\n|1936\n|-\n|''[[The Grapes of Wrath]]''\n|[[John Steinbeck]]\n|1939\n|-\n|''[[Gravity's Rainbow]]''\n|[[Thomas Pynchon]]\n|1973\n|-\n|''[[The Great Gatsby]]''\n|[[F. Scott Fitzgerald]]\n|1925\n|-\n|''[[A Handful of Dust]]''\n|[[Evelyn Waugh]]\n|1934\n|-\n|''[[The Heart Is a Lonely Hunter]]''\n|[[Carson McCullers]]\n|1940\n|-\n|''[[The Heart of the Matter]]''\n|[[Graham Greene]]\n|1948\n|-\n|''[[Herzog_(novel)|Herzog]]''\n|[[Saul Bellow]]\n|1964\n|-\n|''[[Housekeeping (novel)|Housekeeping]]''\n|[[Marilynne Robinson]]\n|1981\n|-\n|''[[A House for Mr. Biswas]]''\n|[[V.S. Naipaul]]\n|1962\n|-\n|''[[I, Claudius]]''\n|[[Robert Graves]]\n|1934\n|-\n|''[[Infinite Jest]]''\n|[[David Foster Wallace]]\n|1996\n|-\n|''[[Invisible Man]]''\n